HEADWORD: Pollux
<hw>Pol"lux</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., the twin
brother of castor; also, the constellation.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A fixed star of the second magnitude, in the
constellation Gemini. Cf. 3d <er>Castor</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Pollucite</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polly</ent>⟦br⟧
